00:00:49.609 --> 00:00:56.009
from small children and their parents and even from grandparents.

00:00:56.009 --> 00:00:58.810
But what about you teenagers?

00:00:58.810 --> 00:01:03.409
You too are still young when compared to adulthood.

00:01:03.409 --> 00:01:09.569
And you are appreciated very much when you show your respect and love for Jehovah.

00:01:09.569 --> 00:01:16.049
Does the Bible indicate anything about Jesus' disposition as a teenager?

00:01:16.049 --> 00:01:20.650
There are comments about him as an infant.

00:01:20.650 --> 00:01:26.450
Also in the book of Luke, it describes Jesus as a child of 12 years old.

00:01:26.450 --> 00:01:37.450
Let's look at that account and determine if it also includes any comments about Jesus' attitude as a teenager.

00:01:37.450 --> 00:01:41.609
In Luke, chapter 2, verse 42,

00:01:41.609 --> 00:01:49.650
it describes Jesus as a pre-teen in saying this.

00:01:49.650 --> 00:01:52.250
Luke 2, 42,

00:01:52.250 --> 00:01:55.530
and when he was 12 years old,

00:01:55.530 --> 00:01:59.170
they went up according to the custom of the festival.

00:01:59.170 --> 00:02:04.329
When the days of the festival were over and they were returning,

00:02:04.329 --> 00:02:08.889
the boy Jesus remained behind in Jerusalem.

00:02:08.889 --> 00:02:12.849
And his parents did not notice it.

00:02:12.849 --> 00:02:19.729
So his parents went looking for him and finally found him three days later.

00:02:19.729 --> 00:02:24.770
What was Jesus focused on as a 12-year-old?

00:02:24.810 --> 00:02:29.250
He was sitting in the temple talking with the teachers about Jehovah.

00:02:29.250 --> 00:02:32.169
Notice verse 47.

00:02:32.169 --> 00:02:42.409
But all those listening to him were in constant amazement at his understanding and his answers.

00:02:42.409 --> 00:02:51.569
What a good example for your children 12 years of age and younger to talk about Jehovah with confidence.

00:02:51.610 --> 00:02:57.129
But what was Jesus' attitude like as a teenager?

00:02:57.129 --> 00:03:02.449
Please follow along in verses 51 and 52.

00:03:02.449 --> 00:03:13.490
Then he, Jesus, went down with them and returned to Nazareth and he continued subject to them.

00:03:13.490 --> 00:03:16.650
That is to his parents.

00:03:16.650 --> 00:03:19.050
How old was he?

00:03:19.090 --> 00:03:20.610
12.

00:03:20.610 --> 00:03:22.009
Well, what comes after 12?

00:03:22.009 --> 00:03:24.210
13.

00:03:24.210 --> 00:03:27.009
Notice verse 52.

00:03:27.009 --> 00:03:30.930
And Jesus went on progressing.

00:03:30.930 --> 00:03:43.289
You see, after 12, he went on progressing in wisdom and in physical growth and in favor with God and man.

00:03:43.330 --> 00:03:50.689
Evidently, then, Jesus was an intelligent well-balanced teenager.

00:03:50.689 --> 00:03:54.569
But who took note of his progress as a teen?

00:03:54.569 --> 00:03:57.849
It said God and man.

00:03:57.849 --> 00:04:05.810
Yes, godly children and teenagers are appreciated by Jehovah and by spiritual men.

00:04:05.810 --> 00:04:12.969
Jehovah and his organization love all you young ones who are striving to do what is right.

00:04:13.009 --> 00:04:18.050
But how do we know that Jehovah loves all of you?

00:04:18.050 --> 00:04:23.089
Well, if you have your Bible, turn to Matthew chapter 19.

00:04:23.089 --> 00:04:30.329
And here we say that Jesus showed his high regard for young ones.

00:04:30.329 --> 00:04:36.649
So Matthew chapter 19, notice verses 13 and 14.

00:04:36.649 --> 00:04:44.970
Then young children were brought to him, for him to place his hands on them and offer prayer.

00:04:44.970 --> 00:04:49.089
But the disciples reprimanded them.

00:04:49.089 --> 00:04:53.089
They did not want the young ones to bother Jesus.

00:04:53.089 --> 00:04:55.689
But notice verse 14.

00:04:55.689 --> 00:05:01.970
Jesus, however, said, let the young children alone.

00:05:01.970 --> 00:05:11.170
And do not try to stop them from coming to me for the kingdom of the heavens belongs to such ones.

00:05:11.170 --> 00:05:14.449
Yes, Jesus welcomed young ones.

00:05:14.449 --> 00:05:19.970
And the Bible tells us that Jesus is the perfect reflection of Jehovah.

00:05:19.970 --> 00:05:24.490
So Jesus was imitating Jehovah's love for young ones.

00:05:24.490 --> 00:05:29.250
After many wise sayings and performing miracles,

00:05:29.250 --> 00:05:36.449
Matthew chapter 21 describes Jesus riding into Jerusalem as Jehovah's anointed one.

00:05:36.449 --> 00:05:42.769
Please notice the difference between some of the adult's reactions and that of appreciative young ones.

00:05:42.769 --> 00:05:49.569
Matthew 21 and verse 15 tells us this.

00:05:49.569 --> 00:05:56.009
